<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-04-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-04-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="262" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d262">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-04-13"><hi rend="italic">April 13,
                            1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>(Mr. Rockhill reports that to the end of March the war claim of Great Britain
                        is £4,800,000; monthly expenses thereafter, £120,000. <pb facs="0375" n="369" xml:id="pg_369"/> Should occupation be continued until the end
                        of the year, £1,600,000 additional.</p>
                    <p>Hopes to get vote next Tuesday on our lump-sum proposition)</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>